All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Administrator
The Administrator class provides administrative operations
AdministratorService
AdministratorService provides an interface for administrators to manage accounts, including creating, deleting, updating, and searching for accounts.
AdminRepository
AdminRepository provides database access methods for administrator account operations such as creating, updating, deleting, and querying accounts.
AdminUI
 
ATMapp
The ATMapp class serves as the main entry point for interacting with the ATM system.
ATMModule
Guice dependency Injection module to bind interfaces to concrete implementations
Customer
The Customer class to handle customer operations and state including updating table balance, and fetching updated values
CustomerRepository
CustomerRepository provides database access methods for customer-related operations
CustomerService
CustomerService provides an interface for customers to manage withdrawals, deposits, and displaying information It implements the IUserService interface.
CustomerUI
 
DatabaseConnection
The DatabaseConnection interface provides a method to obtain a connection to a database.
DatabaseSchema
Database Schema holds the code declaration for the accounts table to execute if it does not exist already
IUserService
IUserService defines a common interface for user services such as AdministratorService or CustomerService.
IUserServiceBuilder
IUserServiceBuilder is responsible for creating instances of IUserService based on the provided account type and user data.
Main
Main class that serves as the entry point for the ATM application.
MySQLConnection
MySQLConnection class implements the DatabaseConnection interface and provides a method to establish a connection to a MySQL database using JDBC.
ServiceBuilder
ServiceBuilder is responsible for creating IUserService objects for either an Administrator or Customer data from the database to determine the appropriate service to be returned.
UI
